<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="615" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,580,883]" box="[160,276,580,606]" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,580,883]" lastBlockId="18.[160,1156,142,375]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="615" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">
<emphasis box="[160,213,615,640]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Male</emphasis>
: Body shining black with a bluish lustre, 
<quantity box="[690,804,615,640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" unit="mm" value="7.25" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="6.0">6–8.5 mm</quantity>
in length (
<figureCitation box="[934,1043,615,640]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[168,1147,143,1287]" captionTargetId="figure-149@24.[166,1149,142,1291]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Anthrax spp., habitus: (a) A. aethiops bezzii; (b) A. dentatus; (c) A. greatheadi; (d) A. lucidus; (e) A. melanistus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477423/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(e)). Frons dusted grey above the antennae and silvery white at eye margins, black haired. Face dusted silvery white and black haired at lower margin. Scutum and scutellum exclusively with sparse black hairs and bristles. Anterior margin of scutum blackish haired. Pleura grey dusted on lower part, black haired. Wings clear with very faint indication of small spots on cross-vein r-m, origin of vein R2+3, and radial sector and anterior branch of cubitus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="24.[160,225,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[168,1147,143,1287]" captionTargetId="figure-149@24.[166,1149,142,1291]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 15. Anthrax spp., habitus: (a) A. aethiops bezzii; (b) A. dentatus; (c) A. greatheadi; (d) A. lucidus; (e) A. melanistus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477423/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(e)). Subcostal cell faint yellow-brown. Plumula black with whitish tips. Abdomen with sparse black hairs, and corners of 1st tergite with tufts of black hairs; tergites 2–4 with short black scaly hairs, but tergites 5–7 with dense brown-yellow scales on sides; posterior margins of tergites with fairly long, black bristles. Gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[891,998,177,202]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[160,225,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[169,1148,941,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-239@17.[166,1149,940,1617]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Anthrax melanistus: (a) gonocoxites, ventral view; (b) tip of epiphallus, dorsal view; (c) tip of epiphallus, lateral view; (d) spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477413/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="615">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(a)) quadratic, with two apical prolongations with normal black, short, spine-like setae apically; epiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[207,314,246,271]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[160,225,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[169,1148,941,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-239@17.[166,1149,940,1617]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Anthrax melanistus: (a) gonocoxites, ventral view; (b) tip of epiphallus, dorsal view; (c) tip of epiphallus, lateral view; (d) spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477413/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="615">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(b,c)) with spines at the tip.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477413" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5477413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477413/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" startId="17.[160,225,1649,1672]" targetBox="[169,1148,941,1616]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1649,1701]" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1649,1672]" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Figure 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[267,450,1649,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanistus">
<emphasis box="[267,450,1649,1672]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">Anthrax melanistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (a) gonocoxites, ventral view; (b) tip of epiphallus, dorsal view; (c) tip of epiphallus, lateral view; (d) spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,142,375]" pageId="18" pageNumber="615">
<emphasis box="[192,270,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="615">Female</emphasis>
: Similar to male; however, upper part of frons narrower than in male and abdomen entirely without scales. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[742,857,316,341]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[160,225,1649,1672]" captionTargetBox="[169,1148,941,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-239@17.[166,1149,940,1617]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Anthrax melanistus: (a) gonocoxites, ventral view; (b) tip of epiphallus, dorsal view; (c) tip of epiphallus, lateral view; (d) spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5477413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5477413/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="615">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(d)) with an egg-shaped, strongly sclerotised bulb, slightly constricted at lower third.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
